properties.name: Central Park
properties.description: Posted by Baostar   Northpark - Central ParkThis paseo run through the heart of the village where I live. It is lined with tall 60-years-old eucalyptus trees and serve as a nice place for a jog or walk. You can see the hills every steps of the way if you\'re walking north (opposite direction).

properties.name: Edible Landscape Garden
properties.description: Posted by Baostar    15058 Harvard Ave. Irvine, CAThe Incredible Edible Park operates year round, 6 days a week. As many as 1,200 volunteers work at a time. If you wish to help feed the hungry in Orange County, contact Sharon, with Second Harvest Food Bank Orange County, at (714) 771-1343. More information is also available at www.FeedOC.org. For information about other opportunities to volunteer in Orange County, contact the Volunteer Center Orange County at (714) 953-5757 or visit www.VolunteerCenter.org. Broccoli, lettuce, potatoes, carrots, beans and squash are among the crops grown at Irvine\'s Incredible Edible Park. People of all ages, including many school children, have helped plant, weed and harvest produce. Second Harvest Food Bank of Orange County distributes the food to the needy.

properties.name: Edwards Irvine Spectrum 21 & IMAX
properties.description: Posted by Baostar  65 Fortune Drive, Irvine, CA 92618A great movie theater and hang out spot at the Irvine Spectrum.

properties.name: Fashion Island
properties.description: Posted by Baostar 401 Newport Center Drive Newport Beach CA, 92660 In the heart of Newport Beach is Fashion Island, offering unique shopping and dining in a beautiful open-air atmosphere. Often referred to as the town center of Newport Beach, Fashion Island is the ultimate outdoor coastal shopping destination with an ocean view and nearly 200 stores. You’ll find Orange County’s only Neiman Marcus, Bloomingdale’s, as well as numerous exclusive boutiques such as American Rag Cie, Juicy Couture, Kate Spade, Original Penguin, Charriol, Martin + Osa, and many others. Shop the exclusive designer stores and boutiques at Neiman Marcus and Bloomingdale’s, which feature collections such as Prada, Jil Sander, Louis Vuitton, Georgio Armani, Chanel, YSL and Dolce & Gabbana. Shoppers can discover the latest lines from Roberto Cavalli, Valentino, Manolo Blahnik and Chloe.

properties.name: Fashion Island's 115-foot Christmas tree
properties.description: Posted by Baostar Nation\'s tallest Christmas tree stands here (between Neiman Marcus and Bloomingdales) every year during holidays. The tree is about 115-foot, weighs about 22,000 pounds, and decorated with 17,000 lights, bows and ornaments.

properties.name: Food Court at the Market Place
properties.description: Posted by Baostar  A nice lunch spot for semi-fast food.

properties.name: Gelson's
properties.description: Posted by Baostar  5521 Alton Parkway, IrvineGelson\'s store is all about cleanliness, convenience, and service. You\'ll find unusual ingredients, special spices, and gourmet foods from the service deli like spiral ham and rib roast. The bakery offers an array of pastries and cakes that you can enjoy with coffee and sit by a cozy fireplace if you just want to relax.

properties.name: Hicks Canyon Trail
properties.description: Posted by Baostar   This trail is right outside of the private residental community where I live. It is accessible from the inside along the corridors, as well as from the outside at Hicks Canyon Park or Citrusglen Park. The original trail was the road from nowhere to nowhere through orange groves (since replaced by houses) and is a favorite jogging trail of many local residents. This may be the least noisy trail in town with few busy streets (and none that you have to cross) and no freeways nearby. Pungent eucalyptus trees line most of the trail and provide shade in the afternoon.

properties.name: Hoag Memorial Hospital
properties.description: Posted by Baostar One Hoag Drive, Newport Beach, CAA great hospital located on the bayside bluffs overlooking Newport Beach.

properties.name: Irvine Barclay Theatre
properties.description: Posted by Baostar 4242 Campus Dr, Irvine, CA 92612The Barclay is a marvelous local theater that brings a wide variety of entertainers and performers to Orange County. Home to the UC Irvine\'s drama department and to Ballet Pacifica, many nationally recognized comedians also make tours stops at the Barclay. Chamber music and opera are regular calendar offerings, as the facility\'s intimate size and good acoustics make every audience member feel close to the action.

properties.name: Irvine Farmer's Market
properties.description: Posted by Baostar   Campus Dr, IrvineFarmer\'s market I go to is at the University Center on the corner of Bridge and Campus (across from UCI). Here you can get vegetables, fruit, mushrooms, fresh herbs, meat, fish, dairy, eggs, honey and plants from farmers in the region of Orange County. Great fun if it\'s not too crowded.

properties.name: Irvine Market Place
properties.description: Posted by Baostar  The Marketplace is huge shopping and entertainment center. The Edwards Cinema and adjacent eating area is a gathering point for teenagers and families. At night, you can see the Marketplace lit up by neon lights like the strips in Las Vegas. But by contrast, the city goes on a virtual lockdown by 10:00 pm and walking at night is an activity prone to police advisory. "How old are you? You\'re not supposed to be out after 10:00 pm." The police cars in Irvine are all white except for a bluegreen-white-blue stripe (Irvine official colors) running the length of the car on the side. And what\'s funny is that they will call for backups in any situations - if you\'re crossing the street illegally, expect at least 3 patrol cars on your punk ass.

properties.name: Irvine Open Space Preserve Nature Center
properties.description: Posted by Baostar  1 Sunnyhill Drive, Irvine, CAThe Irvine Open Space Preserve Nature Center is located at the base of the San Joaquin Hills in Irvine, and serves as a community resource for environmental interest and concern. The five-acre nature preserve is both a home for wildlife and an outdoor classroom where visitors and program participants learn to protect our natural environment. (949) 724-6738

properties.description: Posted by Baostar 936 Avocado Ave, Newport Beach, CAAll the Italian lines in this store are exclusive to brother-and-sister team Emanuela and Alberto Uboldi, former architects who opened the Corona del Mar store in 1999 and a West Hollywood branch in 2002. The Uboldis\' sister, Federica, lives in Italy and sends over the products she finds. Best-sellers here are handmade leather sofas.

properties.name: Jeffrey Open Space Trail
properties.description: Posted by Baostar   10601 Jeffrey Rd, Irvine, CA 92602Bordering the east side of Jeffrey Road, the Jeffrey Open Space Trail is a recreation and open space corridor park that will span Irvine\'s entire north-south length. This rare community amenity will make it possible for residents (if they\'re so inclined and can muster the stamina) to bicycle, jog or walk, literally, from one end of the city to the other. As envisioned in concept, the trail will ultimately link up with trails leading deep into the vast preserved wildlands north and south of the city. Thus, a unique sage to sea outdoor experience will emerge. The trail will feature a dual trail system: an 11-foot-wide paved trail for bicyclists, and a parallel five-foot-wide unpaved path for joggers and walkers. At numerous points, the trail will pass through cool wooded areas and open to small and large parks and grassy meadows. At these picturesque junctures, residents will be able to enjoy picnics, kite flying and other passive recreational activities.

properties.name: John Wayne Airport
properties.description: Posted by BaostarJohn Wayne Airport has one of the shortest runways, at 5,701 feet, restricting its commercial use to aircraft no larger than a Boeing 757. The short runway length, combined with noise restrictions, requires an unusual takeoff at or near full power, with a steep climb followed by a sudden reduction in power and a sharp turn.

properties.name: Ligne Roset
properties.description: Posted by Baostar Newport Center Drive, Newport Beach, CA 92660A new Ligne Roset store just opened at Fashion Island. I happen to stumbled upon it and saw a dinning table by Didier Gomez that I absolutely love. I\'m going back there to see about ordering a set from France. Update: I did purchase the dinning table and waited about 3 months for it to shipped over from France. Here\'s a picture of Blinky sitting on it. :)

properties.name: Lucca Cafe
properties.description: Posted by Baobot  6507 Quail Hill Pkwy., Irvine, CA, United StatesLucca Cafe is tucked in the corner of the Quail Hill Village Center. The white-tableclothed tables at Lucca are set against shades of lemon and moss on the walls. The café prides itself on using many organic and hormone- and pesticide-free ingredients.

properties.name: Main Beach
properties.description: Posted by Baostar   Laguna Beach\'s two-acre waterfront park is linked to Heisler Park, a two-mile greenway that runs along the bluffs of the coastline. The Broadway intersection is a focal point with lots of pedestrian traffic. There are 30 art galleries, antique shops and boutiques, The Crawl of pubs, and fine restaurants. The Main Street and small town atmosphere here makes it a great public gathering space where the personalities are rich - not always admirable, of course, but rich.

properties.name: My commute in Irvine
properties.description: Posted by BaostarIrvine, CAThis is what my commute looks like when I worked a Cardservice. To the left is John Wayne Airport; turn right on Michelson Dr and you\'ll find a tiny, drive-thru coffee hut and a realm of office buildings.

properties.name: Northpark Village
properties.description: Posted by Baostar    A private residential community where I live, situated within 60-year-old strands of eucalyptus windrows, and align to give homes beautiful views of the foothills. It\'s a 275-acre community with 1600 homes, 11 private parks, 6 swimming pools, tennis courts, clubhouse, and other amenities. There are a variety of architecture styles reminiscent of "Classic California" neighborhoods such as Pasadena, San Marino, Santa Monica, and so on. You\'ll find that all the streets are named after different places in California...and the pools...and the parks. Hicks Canyon Elementary School is adjacent to the community so kids can actually walk to school without going outside the neighborhoods. Right outside is Hicks Canyon public park where parents usually watch baseball and soccer games; there are biking trails that lead to the foothills on both sides; and a local shopping center. The community is also very pedestrian and dog-friendly - residents like to walk to the grocery store, or their dogs, or kids in strollers at anytime of the day. 1/2 block away is my favorite coffee shop, Champagne Bakery, and 1 1/2 block away is my favorite bookstore.

properties.name: Sherman Library & Gardens
properties.description: Posted by Baostar   2647 East Coast Highway Corona Del Mar, CA 92625Sherman Library & Gardens is a 2.2 acre Corona del Mar horticultural retreat. The Gardens provide a museum of living plants, displayed amidst a setting of immaculate gardens, patios and conservatories linked together by wide brick walkways, beds blooming with seasonal flowers and bubbling tile fountains. The Library is a specialized research center devoted to the study of the Pacific Southwest.

properties.name: Sky Divers at Fashion Island
properties.description: Posted by Baostar This bronze sculpture of three figures posed on 27 ft. concrete columns is located near Bloomingdales at Fashion Island. It is inspired by circus aerialists and was commissioned in 1967 by Aristides Demetrios.

properties.name: The Bluffs
properties.description: Posted by Baostar  100 Villagio, Newport BeachThis is where I stayed when I quit my job and went on a hiatus in 1999. A couple of my friends left their day jobs to start their own company, which was based in a luxurious 2 bedrooms apartment. We mostly sat by the pool and drank, rode the exercise bikes, and watched movies in the private surround-sound theater.

properties.name: The Groves Antique Flea Market
properties.description: Posted by Baostar 5500 Irvine Center Drive, Irvine CA 92618It\'s worth the rummage. My friend Angie loves to go there and managed to drag me along once or twice. You\'ll find things like refurbished armoires, buffets and dressers, and cool smaller items like jars, mirrors, trays, vintage accessories, postcards and pottery. It is held the first Sunday of each month from 7 a.m. to 2 p.m. at Irvine Valley College, 5500 Irvine Center Dr. Admission and parking are free. For more information call (949) 786-5277.

properties.name: Wholesome Choice Market
properties.description: Posted by Baostar  18040 Culver Drive, Irvine, CAWholesome Choice offers American brands, plus an impressive line of Asian, Mediterranean, Russian, Eastern European, and even have South African foods. They have the natural and organic foods you\'ve come to expect, along with delicious market-fresh produce that arrives daily. There\'s a hearthstone bakery, located at the front of the store, where you can see speciality breads baked throughout the day. Their international food court caters to all cultures and all the locals can be typically seen eating in the dining area.
